                <td bgColor="#ECECEC"><textarea cols="48" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL" onselect="storeCaret(this);" onclick="storeCaret(this);" onkeyup="storeCaret(this);" onchange="storeCaret(this);">[quote][i]Originally posted by Zerp[/i]
[br]Is it just me to miss the old travelling days? 
I remember playing this game for a month or so as a ranger woodelf before finally making it to the docks in BB. And then seeing the boat.. I was like... wtf is that. I remember getting on the boat, making it to EC and meeting some guys and them saying "Woot long way for a lev 10 ranger... you are far from home". And then finding the tunnell and being even more surprised at the bazaar... well, the bazaar that was there then. A little later I died to some ghouls trying to make it to wc. Was not able to make it back within the 6 hour timer and lost my corpse and all the crap on it.

I remember making my first ikky, and deciding to travel to EC to buy some gear. It took the whole evening to get there, but I was happy.

I remember finding out about the pots room, endlessly swimming there. I was bound there, died tons of times to that dragon I dont even remember the name of now. People always wondered how the heck could i make it to any city in a min or two...

Even more, I miss when Sullon Zek made some sense. When it took guts to take your necro to Mistmoore. When people who had played for months or even years had never been past Gfay. When you could hold 4-5 entry points and seal off Kunark. 

My point: of all the nerfs/upgrades that have spoiled this game, I think the ease of travelling has been the biggest spoiler of them all. Norrath used to feel like a big, misterious world. 
Now, it feels as deep and meaningful as the collection of Arenas in Quake 3. More of a collection of levels, rooms and zones, than a breathing, scary, mysterious world to discover and explore.
[/quote]</textarea><br /></td>
              </tr>
