emeber thinking some day Ill go to the great divide and kill me one of those shardwurms.  Or thinking that the Euridites must get lonely so far away.  Or evil gnomes must have to hire a porter thier first day and do the wine quest.  <br /><br />I also remeber having to think what zones are the best way to get somewhere.<br /><br />OT to DL for nexus.  Should I go OT, SF, BW, DL?  OT, FM, DL?  Oggok to Seb was fun too.  OT to seb was tough cause newts would be waiting for ya.  A port to ej was almost always hard to find so you had to go OT, WW, FOB, then pray that EJ was free of pks.  But if was not then had to knowthe way from the swamp.<br /><br />Now it is so easy to go to most places it makes travel boring.  It was challanging to go places.  The world seemed vast.  Now it is too small, that is why they make so many expansions.  Imagine if you had to run 1 hour to get from PoTactics to BoT or if you are lucky find a port for 100plat and cut the time to 10 minutes.  Imagine having to run through PoJ to get to PoV to get to HoH.  OR PoJ to PoS to BoT.  It would be more challanging.  I also hate grave yards.  No need for necros anymore.<br /><br />I also hate that players under 10 dont lose thioer corpse in 30 min, spawn with all thier gear already, and dont lose any exp.  They have dumbed down this game too much.  I am constantly trying new things to try and make it challanging again.  I hope and pray that eq2 is more like what eq was 2 years ago.  Seeing a new race was exiting.  Your a lizard man, that is so cool.  That is what a dark elf looks like?  Why are you so short?  Oh you are a gnome.  Imagine it taking getting to level 20 before you see another race than yours because it is too dangerous to get to mutual zone areas.<br /><br />The first time I saw a dark elf I was level 12 in Feerott killing the lizards for tails outside CT.  He was level 20 and was headed into CT.  I asked him w]what level he was and his class.  He was a lvl 20 enchanter.  He was nervous because he never been so far from Nek forest before.  This is how it should be.  Worring that you are too far away or are taking to big a risk made this game fun.  Not that it is gone the only way to get that feeling again is to try and solo things that used to take a full raid to do.  But that gets dull fast.<br /><br />I want a PoK restriction.  All level 40s and under cant zone in.  You cant go into PoT until level 55.  Instead of flags make keys and make people travel through the flag prgression to get to the zones.  No more GYs as well, the idea is just stupid.  CRs are supposed to be hard!!!!!!<br /><br />I still like this game, but it is not nearly as interesting and fun as it used to be.</span></font></td>
