                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;09/29/2003&nbsp;: 3:12:57 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> The 3 biggest accomplishments early on for me were:<br /><br />1.  Traveling to Ak'Anon at 12 to buy a spell when KOS in there<br />2.  Ditto at 16<br />3.  Getting to the Overthere at 16 to buy Banshee Aura... what a CR that would have been, bound on Odus<br /><br />While the KOS in Ak'Anon isn't trivialized by PoP, the danger of traveling there is.<br /><br />I agree that travel should get easier as you spend more time in the game.  I wish it were through quests (like the PoK gate items) and not through the simple act of shelling out real $$ for expansions.<br /></span></font></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2">Rylok1</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;09/29/2003&nbsp;: 2:38:45 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Ah, the good old days...  <br /><br />The game was a lot different back then.  The world seemed huge and mysterious.  I remember running my level 5 Iksar Shaman to FP because my friends were there, what a run that was.  The first time I got on a boat was an exciting experience, but after a few long waits, it got old.  I think that after a few long runs or long waits it lost it's novelty and it was just a burden.  I have a lot of good memories about the old days, but I wouldn't go back.<br /> <br />But, even with that being said, I do think that people starting the game after Luclin, and especially after PoP, have missed out on something.  <br />You really felt isolated in some areas, and it really felt like it was you against the "environment".  There was a real sense of adventure every time you logged on.  The game has turned into more of a rat race for levels/loot and less about adventures.  <br />I still have fun playing the game.  It's just a different kind of experience now, but LDON has done a lot to renew the feeling of adventure in the game.  <br />I'm glad I was able to experience the "Golden Age?" of EQ.<br /><br /><br />Rylok Darklyte<br />65 Arch Lich<br />Divine Blade - Lanys<br /><br />Zeran Spiritblade<br />56 Shaman<br />Divine Blade - Lanys</span></font></td>
